






<p>The third Children Sports &amp; Games Festival was held on Wednesday October 
7, 2009 in Sport Hall of Hejab with presence of Sport for All Association of 
Tehran and Iran Sport for All Federation.</p>
<p>According to the Public Relations of Iran Sport for All Federation, more than 
a thousand children from kindergartens throughout Tehran City attended the great 
event and performed children sport and games. </p>
<p>The two previous festivals were held with cooperation of Tehran Sport for All 
Association and Children Sports and Games Association.Â  The last festival was 
held in Kerman Province in late July 2009 with the presence of 3300 children 
throughout all kindergartens of Kerman City which has broken the record of 
Sweden children with the 3000 children.</p>
<p>Mr. Mehdi Azar Barzin, the Head of Children Sports & Games Association 
expressed hope that this association can provide happiness and mirthfulness for 
children across the country.</p>